  <section id="terms-body" style="background:white;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">

      <div class="terms-section">
        <p>These Terms and Conditions ("Agreement") govern your use of the services provided by Jake Fixes Tech LLC, a limited liability company organized under the laws of the State of New Hampshire. By using our services you agree to be bound by this Agreement in its entirety. If you do not agree, do not use our services.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- PART 1 -->
      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.5rem;color:#2563eb;border-bottom:2px solid #dbeafe;padding-bottom:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Part 1: Tech Repair Services</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
        <p>By bringing your device to Jake Fixes Tech LLC, scheduling a service appointment, or authorizing any repair work in person, by phone, by text or by email, you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. Your authorization to proceed with a repair constitutes acceptance of this Agreement.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>2. Diagnostic Fee</h2>
        <p>A non-refundable diagnostic fee of <strong>$50</strong> is charged for all repair assessments. This fee covers the time and expertise required to evaluate your device. If you choose to proceed with the recommended repair, the $50 fee will be credited toward your total repair cost. If you decline the repair after diagnosis, the diagnostic fee is retained in full as payment for services rendered. No exceptions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>3. Pricing & Payment</h2>
        <p>Jake Fixes Tech LLC charges flat-rate pricing for all repair services. All labor fees are due and payable before repair work begins. Parts and components required for a repair are charged separately and will be communicated to you in advance before any parts are ordered or installed. We accept cash, credit/debit card and other payment methods agreed upon in writing.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>All sales are final once work has begun.</strong> No refunds will be issued for completed labor. If you are dissatisfied with a repair, your sole remedy is the 30-day labor warranty described in Section 5.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>Chargebacks:</strong> Initiating a chargeback or payment dispute for services legitimately rendered is a breach of this Agreement. Jake Fixes Tech LLC reserves the right to pursue collection of any disputed amount plus associated fees and costs through all available legal remedies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="terms-section">
        <h2>4. Data Loss & Backup Responsibility</h2>
        <p><strong>You are solely responsible for backing up all data on your device before submitting it for any service.</strong> Jake Fixes Tech LLC is not responsible for any data loss, corruption or inaccessibility that occurs during or as a result of the repair process, regardless of cause.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">By leaving your device with us, you acknowledge and accept that data loss is an inherent risk of repair work. You release Jake Fixes Tech LLC, its owner and agents from any and all liability related to lost, corrupted, deleted or otherwise inaccessible data. This release applies even if data loss results from technician error.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">If data backup or recovery services are requested, they will be quoted and billed separately.</p>
      </div>

